---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<Base title="Important Information | Mortgages with JJ" description="Public disclosure for JJ van der Westhuizen, Senior Mortgage Adviser under Mortgage Design Limited (FSP752291) — services, fees, commissions, conflicts and complaints. Required under the Financial Markets Conduct Act.">
	<Fragment slot="head">
		<meta name="robots" content="noindex,follow" />
	</Fragment>

	<PageHero
		trail={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Important Information' }]}
		eyebrow="Important information"
		title="Important Information"
		lede="Who I am, what I do, how I'm paid, and how to raise a concern. Required disclosure under the Financial Markets Conduct Act."
	/>

	<section class="light" id="legal">
		<div class="wrap">
			<article class="post-body">
    <h2>Who I am</h2>

          <div class="mwj-info-identity">
            <div class="mwj-info-identity-card">
              <p class="label">The adviser</p>
              <p class="name">JJ van der Westhuizen</p>
              <p class="meta">Senior Mortgage Adviser<br>FSP1000031</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mwj-info-identity-card">
              <p class="label">The licensed FAP</p>
              <p class="name">Mortgage Design Limited</p>
              <p class="meta">Licensed Financial Advice Provider<br>FSP752291</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>I provide financial advice as an authorised body under <strong>Mortgage Design Limited</strong> (FSP752291), a Licensed Financial Advice Provider authorised by the Financial Markets Authority (FMA) under the Financial Markets Conduct Act.</p>

          <h3>Office contact details</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Mortgage Design Limited</strong><br>
            Address: 44B Rame Road, Greenhithe, Auckland<br>
            Phone: <a href="tel:+6498734613">09 873 4613</a><br>
            Email: <a href="mailto:info@mortgagedesign.co.nz">info@mortgagedesign.co.nz</a><br>
            Website: <a href="https://www.mortgagedesign.co.nz" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.mortgagedesign.co.nz</a>
          </p>

          <h2>Nature and scope of financial advice services</h2>

          <h3>The services I provide</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Debt management — including borrowing for personal and investment purposes</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Products I can provide financial advice about</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Home loans</li>
            <li>Investment loans</li>
            <li>Construction loans</li>
            <li>KiwiSaver investments</li>
            <li>Managed investments</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Product providers I might recommend</h3>
          <div class="mwj-info-lenders">
            <span>ANZ</span>
            <span>ASB</span>
            <span>BNZ</span>
            <span>Westpac</span>
            <span>Kiwibank</span>
            <span>Co-operative Bank</span>
            <span>SBS</span>
            <span>TSB</span>
            <span>HSBC</span>
            <span>Bank of China</span>
            <span>Heartland Bank</span>
            <span>ASAP Finance</span>
            <span>Avanti Finance</span>
            <span>Liberty</span>
            <span>Pepper Money</span>
            <span>Resimac</span>
            <span>Basecorp</span>
            <span>Southern Cross Partners</span>
            <span>Cressida Capital</span>
            <span>DBR</span>
            <span>First Mortgage Trust</span>
            <span>Funding Partners</span>
            <span>NZCU</span>
            <span>Plus Finance</span>
            <span>Prospa</span>
            <span>NZ Funds</span>
            <span>Booster</span>
            <span>Milford Asset Management</span>
            <span>Generate</span>
          </div>

          <h3>Trusted referral partners</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Tower (Fire &amp; General insurance)</li>
            <li>XE Money</li>
          </ul>
          <p>In some cases, I may receive a referral fee or commission for connecting you with a referral partner. I will explain how this fee or commission is calculated before proceeding.</p>

          <h2>Fees</h2>
          <p>The fees for advice and services depend on the nature and scope of what is provided. I will always discuss and agree on fees with you before beginning any work and clearly explain how payments are made.</p>
          <p>Where fees apply, they may be based on a combination of:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>A set dollar amount; or</li>
            <li>A percentage-based fee</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The agreed advice and service fees may include charges for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Initial advice and ongoing service; or</li>
            <li>Annual advice and services</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Other costs</h3>
          <p>If additional costs arise while providing advice, I will confirm these with you beforehand. I do not charge clients directly for the financial advice itself unless agreed otherwise.</p>

          <h2>Commissions</h2>
          <p>On settlement of a loan, I usually receive commission from the applicable lender. The commission is generally upfront, but may also include a trail commission.</p>
          <p>I may also receive a fixed-rate rollover fee from the applicable lender if I assist in refixing your loan.</p>
          <p>I may also receive a referral fee or commission payment if I refer you to one of the referral partners listed above. I will give you more information about how that referral fee or commission is calculated before proceeding.</p>

          <h3>Commission ranges</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Upfront commission</strong> — a percentage of the value of your loan balance, between 0.55% and 0.85%</li>
            <li><strong>Trail commission</strong> — a percentage of the value of your outstanding loan amount, calculated at the end of each month in which you hold the loan, between 0.15% and 0.20%</li>
            <li><strong>Refix fee</strong> — some providers pay a fixed rate of $150 if I assist you in re-fixing your loan</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>When I have to repay commission to the lender</h3>
          <p>In the event that, in the 28-month period following drawdown of your loan, your loan is fully or partially repaid or the terms materially changed, and a lender requires that I repay the applicable commission to them, we may charge you a one-off fee.</p>
          <p>Any such fee would be no more than $3,500 (plus GST, if any) and would be calculated based on a rate of $300 (plus GST, if any) per hour of my time spent providing financial advice to you in connection with the applicable loan. The fee charged to you will not exceed the amount of commission I have to repay to the lender.</p>
          <p>Should you choose to use my services and then decide to go directly to any lender or use another adviser, you remain liable for the time involved at the hourly rate. Any collection costs, interest, or late payment fees and charges applicable will be payable by you.</p>
          <p><em>Financial Advisers under Mortgage Design's FAP are paid a flat-rate commission or a base salary (or both) to ensure they seek the best product and lender for the client.</em></p>

          <h2>Managing conflicts of interest</h2>
          <p>I place clients' interests first, though I maintain professional relationships with product providers. From time to time, providers may support conferences or training for advisers under the Mortgage Design FAP.</p>
          <p>To manage conflicts of interest, we:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Follow a clear advice process based on your goals and circumstances</li>
            <li>Recommend products that suit your needs, regardless of commission received</li>
            <li>Provide annual training on managing conflicts</li>
            <li>Maintain registers for conflicts, gifts, and incentives, monitored regularly</li>
            <li>Undergo annual independent compliance assurance reviews</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Duties and obligations</h2>
          <p>As a licensed provider, Mortgage Design (and the advisers operating under its FAP, including JJ) is bound by the Financial Markets Conduct Act to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Meet the standards of competence, knowledge, and skill set out in the Code of Conduct</li>
            <li>Give priority to the client's interests</li>
            <li>Exercise care, diligence, and skill</li>
            <li>Meet the standards of ethical behaviour, conduct, and client care set out in the Code of Conduct</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Complaints process</h2>

          <h3>Internal complaints</h3>
          <p>If you have a problem, concern, or complaint about any part of my advice or service, please tell me first so I can try to fix the problem.</p>
          <p>If we cannot resolve the matter directly, Mortgage Design's internal complaints manager is <strong>Clayton D'Lima</strong>. He can be reached at <a href="mailto:complaints@mortgagedesign.co.nz">complaints@mortgagedesign.co.nz</a> or 021 175 9559. Clayton will reply within 24 to 48 hours.</p>
          <p>The internal complaints handling process is:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Acknowledge your complaint</li>
            <li>Review the information</li>
            <li>Try to come to a resolution</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>External complaints</h3>
          <p>If a resolution is not reached internally, or you prefer, you can contact <strong>Financial Services Complaints Limited (FSCL)</strong> at no cost. FSCL is an independent dispute resolution scheme approved by the Minister of Consumer Affairs.</p>

          <div class="mwj-info-callout">
            <p><strong>Financial Services Complaints Limited (FSCL)</strong></p>
            <p>Address: PO Box 5967, Wellington 6140</p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:0800347257">0800 347 257</a></p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:complaints@fscl.org.nz">complaints@fscl.org.nz</a></p>
          </div>

          <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #8A8580; margin-top: 48px; text-align: center;">This disclosure information is current as of May 2026 and may be updated from time to time.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>
</Base>

<style>

	.mwj-info-identity {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 16px;
		margin: 1.4em 0 1.8em;
	}
	.mwj-info-identity-card {
		border: 1px solid var(--paper-line);
		border-radius: var(--r);
		padding: 20px 22px;
		background: #fff;
	}
	.mwj-info-identity-card .label {
		font-family: var(--data);
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--gold-ink);
		margin: 0 0 8px;
	}
	.mwj-info-identity-card .name {
		font-family: var(--display);
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--ink);
		margin: 0 0 6px;
	}
	.mwj-info-identity-card .meta {
		font-size: 0.92rem;
		color: var(--on-light-mut);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}
	.mwj-info-lenders {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px;
		margin: 1.1em 0 1.8em;
	}
	.mwj-info-lenders span {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--ink);
		background: var(--paper-2);
		border: 1px solid var(--paper-line);
		border-radius: 999px;
		padding: 6px 12px;
	}
	.mwj-info-callout {
		border: 1px solid var(--paper-line);
		border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
		border-radius: 4px;
		background: var(--paper);
		padding: 18px 22px;
		margin: 1.6em 0;
	}
	.mwj-info-callout p { margin: 0.35em 0; }
	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.mwj-info-identity { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}
</style>
